WEBVTT

00:01.672 --> 00:02.623
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:02.623 --> 00:04.215
Victoria: DAVID!

00:04.215 --> 00:06.127
SO YOU NEVER LOOKED AT PORTER
FOR THE MURDER, HUH?

00:06.127 --> 00:08.219
HE WAS IN WITH REYES AND ME
WHEN GRAYSON GOT WHACKED.

00:08.219 --> 00:10.131
I KNEW YOU'D HAVE
QUESTIONS ABOUT AMANDA.

00:10.131 --> 00:11.262
DID YOU GIVE HER THE MONEY?

00:11.262 --> 00:12.343
I GAVE HER EVERYTHING.

00:12.343 --> 00:13.894
I WANT TO DO SOMETHING
FOR DAVID --

00:13.894 --> 00:15.266
SOMETHING THAT MIGHT GIVE YOU

00:15.266 --> 00:16.977
A WAY AROUND
VICTORIA'S MEDIA BLACKOUT.

00:16.977 --> 00:18.099
I HAVE FOUND A WAY

00:18.099 --> 00:20.231
TO PUT YOUR FATHER'S SCANDAL
BEHIND YOU.

00:20.231 --> 00:21.272
THAT'S THE DEED
TO YOUR BEACH HOUSE.

00:21.272 --> 00:22.273
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

00:22.273 --> 00:23.694
ATONING
FOR MY FATHER'S SINS.

00:23.694 --> 00:25.646
GIVE ME EXCLUSIVE RIGHTS
TO DAVID'S STORY.

00:25.646 --> 00:28.529
PROVIDED YOU GIVE US
FINAL APPROVAL ON ALL STORIES.

00:28.529 --> 00:30.030
Daniel: AND FOR A MINUTE,
I THOUGHT I COULD BE

00:30.030 --> 00:31.412
THE GUY I WAS WITH YOU
YESTERDAY, BUT...

00:31.412 --> 00:33.534
WE KEEP THINGS
STRICTLY PROFESSIONAL.

00:33.534 --> 00:35.206
PLEASE CONNECT ME TO PAGE SIX.

00:35.206 --> 00:37.458
I HAVE A STORY
ABOUT DANIEL GRAYSON.

00:37.458 --> 00:40.000
NEVER THOUGHT I'D BE GOING HOME
WITH CHARLOTTE GRAYSON.

00:40.000 --> 00:42.293
IT'S "CLARKE."
 MY MISTAKE.

00:42.293 --> 00:44.215
Nolan: WHEN ARE YOU
GONNA TELL HIM?
 WHEN HE'S READY.

00:46.006 --> 00:48.219
[ ANGUS & JULIA STONE'S
"FOR YOU" PLAYS ]

00:53.674 --> 00:56.557
♪ IF I TALK REAL SLOWLY ♪

00:59.270 --> 01:02.353
♪ IF I TRY REAL HARD ♪

01:05.025 --> 01:08.899
♪ HERE I GO ♪

01:08.899 --> 01:10.030
DADDY! DADDY!

01:10.030 --> 01:11.532
David: HEY!

01:11.532 --> 01:14.365
OH,
LOOK WHAT YOU FOUND.

01:14.365 --> 01:15.826
BUT HE'S MISSING AN ARM.

01:15.826 --> 01:17.408
YEAH,
BUT HE'S GOT FOUR MORE.

01:17.408 --> 01:19.700
YOU KNOW WHAT'S COOL?
HE'S GONNA GROW THAT ONE BACK.

01:19.700 --> 01:21.122
BUT FIRST,
HE HAS TO GO BACK HOME.

01:23.294 --> 01:24.295
[ GASPS ]

01:24.295 --> 01:26.377
HEY!
I WANTED TO WATCH IT GROW!

01:26.377 --> 01:28.799
OH, YEAH,
BUT THAT TAKES A LONG TIME

01:28.799 --> 01:30.131
AND A LOT OF SALTWATER.

01:30.131 --> 01:31.132
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:31.132 --> 01:33.174
OKAY, THAT'S IT.
COME ON!

01:33.174 --> 01:34.885
AAH!
 [ LAUGHS ]

01:34.885 --> 01:38.889
♪ ...WITH ALL OF YOUR HEART ♪

01:50.110 --> 01:52.112
[ TRAIN HORN BLARES ]

01:52.112 --> 01:54.114
[ TRAIN RATTLING ]

01:55.826 --> 01:58.699
GOOD MORNING.

02:08.048 --> 02:10.631
VINCE?

02:12.513 --> 02:13.924
[ SIGHS ]
THERE YOU ARE.

02:13.924 --> 02:15.015
HEY,
WHERE'S ALL MY STUFF?

02:16.717 --> 02:18.098
MAKE YOURSELF
COMFORTABLE.

02:18.098 --> 02:19.850
NO, I-I GOT TO GET HOME.

02:22.022 --> 02:27.067
I KNOW THIS MUST BE CONFUSING,
ESPECIALLY AFTER LAST NIGHT.

02:27.067 --> 02:29.109
I USUALLY DON'T SLEEP
WITH THE BAIT,

02:29.109 --> 02:30.571
BUT...
HOW COULD I RESIST?

02:30.571 --> 02:33.614
THE BAIT?
BAIT FOR WHAT?

02:33.614 --> 02:37.198
A FISH I'VE BEEN AFTER
FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

02:40.781 --> 02:44.545
GOOD MORNING.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:44.545 --> 02:48.249
I BET THE OCEAN IS HAPPY
TO HAVE YOU BACK IN HER ARMS.

02:48.249 --> 02:49.290
YOU GOT MY MESSAGE.

02:49.290 --> 02:50.751
MM-HMM.

02:52.633 --> 02:54.174
[ SIGHS ]

02:54.174 --> 02:55.466
HOW WAS YOUR FIRST
NIGHT HERE?

02:55.466 --> 02:58.639
SURREAL.

02:58.639 --> 03:02.893
ALMOST LIKE NOTHING
HAD CHANGED.

03:02.893 --> 03:05.306
YOU KNOW,
AFTER YOUR ARREST,

03:05.306 --> 03:07.107
I HELD ON TO THIS PLACE
FOR YEARS.

03:07.107 --> 03:10.110
I USED TO COME
AND STAY HERE FOR HOURS

03:10.110 --> 03:12.813
AND IMAGINE MYSELF
HERE WITH YOU.

03:15.576 --> 03:17.278
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:17.278 --> 03:18.739
I ALWAYS WAS
TOO SENTIMENTAL.

03:18.739 --> 03:20.741
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:24.455 --> 03:27.087
I'VE ARRANGED FOR THE TAILOR
TO COME FOR A FITTING LATER.

03:27.087 --> 03:28.289
TV CREW COMES AT 4:00.

03:28.289 --> 03:31.001
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU SET
THIS UP SO QUICKLY.

03:31.001 --> 03:32.883
WELL, MARGAUX
IS A VERY CLOSE FRIEND.

03:32.883 --> 03:35.886
YOU CAN'T UNDERESTIMATE
THE HUNGER OF THE AUDIENCE

03:35.886 --> 03:37.137
TO KNOW YOUR STORY.

03:39.390 --> 03:41.932
DAVID.

03:41.932 --> 03:43.514
ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO TELL IT?

03:45.145 --> 03:46.727
I NEED TO SET
THE RECORD STRAIGHT.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.519
THERE'S PEOPLE OUT THERE THAT
STILL THINK I'M A TERRORIST.

03:48.519 --> 03:49.520
RIGHT.

03:49.520 --> 03:52.022
THEY NEED TO SEE
THAT I WAS A VICTIM,

03:52.022 --> 03:53.153
THAT I WAS BETRAYED.

03:55.566 --> 03:57.528
[ SIGHS ] YEAH.

03:57.528 --> 03:59.490
WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD
GO OVER SOME TALKING POINTS.

03:59.490 --> 04:01.662
THERE WILL BE MILLIONS
WATCHING, AND --

04:01.662 --> 04:04.825
WELL, THAT'S THE GOOD THING
ABOUT THE TRUTH --

04:04.825 --> 04:06.787
YOU DON'T NEED
TALKING POINTS.

04:08.419 --> 04:11.171
I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT.

04:16.255 --> 04:18.137
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

04:18.137 --> 04:19.259
HACKING INTO THE FBI

04:19.259 --> 04:23.143
SHOULD GET HARDER
AS I GET OLDER, BUT...NOPE.

04:23.143 --> 04:25.806
WHAM, BAM,
THANKS, UNCLE SAM.

04:25.806 --> 04:28.689
WOULD YOU DO IF YOUR BESTIE
WASN'T A KEYBOARD COWBOY,

04:28.689 --> 04:31.151
BESIDES, WELL,
ACTUALLY TALK TO YOUR FATHER?

04:31.151 --> 04:33.654
I TOLD YOU,
I'M GIVING HIM SPACE.

04:33.654 --> 04:36.737
AND DOWNLOADING HIS CONFIDENTIAL
PSYCHIATRIC ASSESSMENT

04:36.737 --> 04:39.109
ISN'T AN INVASION
OF SAID SPACE?

04:39.109 --> 04:41.161
I WANT TO HELP HIM,
AND IN ORDER TO DO THAT,

04:41.161 --> 04:43.163
I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT HE'S BEEN THROUGH.

04:43.163 --> 04:44.204
[ SIGHS ]

04:44.204 --> 04:46.577
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN
HIS WOUNDS, NOLAN.

04:48.208 --> 04:50.080
YOU MEAN THESE?

04:50.080 --> 04:52.913
IT SAYS THESE BASTARDS
WHIPPED HIM WITH CHAINS.

04:52.913 --> 04:54.214
LET'S SEE THE INTERVIEW.

04:54.214 --> 04:55.676
I CAN BARELY
STOMACH THIS, EMS.

04:55.676 --> 04:57.127
I DON'T THINK WE SHOULD
WATCH THIS VIDEO.

04:57.127 --> 04:58.549
NO, I NEED TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED.

04:58.549 --> 05:00.421
AND I WANT TO HEAR IT
FROM HIM.

05:01.972 --> 05:03.013
[ MOUSE CLICKS ]

05:03.013 --> 05:04.925
WELL, THEN, LET IT PLAY.

05:04.925 --> 05:06.477
PLEASE.

05:06.477 --> 05:09.930
YOU CAN'T DO THIS TO ME.
I'M ONLY 19.

05:09.930 --> 05:11.101
I'M JUST STARTING MY LIFE.

05:11.101 --> 05:13.814
I JUST GOT MY FATHER BACK.

05:13.814 --> 05:15.606
PLEASE.

05:15.606 --> 05:17.488
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE TRYING
TO DO HERE --

05:17.488 --> 05:20.030
SPOUT OFF A BUNCH
OF PERSONAL DETAILS,

05:20.030 --> 05:23.033
MAKE YOURSELF SEEM
LIKE A REAL PERSON.

05:25.155 --> 05:26.747
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.046
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

05:38.839 --> 05:39.880
Vince: [ CHUCKLES ]

05:39.880 --> 05:41.672
WHERE WAS THIS ENTHUSIASM
LAST NIGHT?

05:41.672 --> 05:43.554
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
 GO AHEAD, KID.

05:43.554 --> 05:45.386
LET'S SEE
IF YOU CAN GET IT.

05:45.386 --> 05:46.887
AAH!

05:53.143 --> 05:54.234
BITCH!

05:55.025 --> 05:56.477
AAH! AAH!

06:00.691 --> 06:03.614
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

06:08.118 --> 06:09.450
[ GROANS ]

06:11.161 --> 06:14.455
OH, MY GOD.

06:26.096 --> 06:27.968
Woman:
 WHILE YOU WERE INCARCERATED,

06:27.968 --> 06:30.641
WOULD YOU SAY
YOUR PRIMARY EMOTION WAS FEAR?

06:30.641 --> 06:33.063
ANGER? HELPLESSNESS?

06:33.063 --> 06:36.186
UH, FEAR, AT FIRST...

06:36.186 --> 06:39.069
THAT I WOULDN'T SEE
THE SUN AGAIN OR...

06:39.069 --> 06:41.111
THAT I WOULDN'T BE ABLE
TO SURVIVE THE TORTURE.

06:41.111 --> 06:43.153
THEN, OVER TIME,
I WOULD STOP FEELING.

06:43.153 --> 06:45.446
AND NOW,
SINCE YOU'VE BEEN OUT?

06:45.446 --> 06:47.027
[ SIGHS ]

06:47.027 --> 06:51.291
I KNOW THAT I'M SUPPOSED
TO FEEL RELIEVED AND THANKFUL.

06:51.291 --> 06:53.333
BUT I'M -- I DON'T.

06:53.333 --> 06:56.917
I FEEL MORE ALONE OUT HERE
THAN I EVER FELT IN THERE.

06:56.917 --> 06:58.168
HAVE YOU FOUND YOURSELF

06:58.168 --> 07:01.632
PRONE TO MOOD SWINGS,
VIOLENT IMPULSES?

07:05.095 --> 07:07.217
THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME.
WE'RE DONE.

07:08.469 --> 07:09.640
[ SIGHS ]

07:09.640 --> 07:12.603
SO, WHAT WAS
HIS DIAGNOSIS?

07:12.603 --> 07:15.646
[ MOUSE CLICKS ]
 Nolan: UM...COMPLEX PTSD.

07:15.646 --> 07:17.397
"PSYCHOLOGICAL FRAGMENTATION,

07:17.397 --> 07:20.230
A LOSS OF A SENSE
OF SAFETY AND TRUST."

07:20.230 --> 07:21.732
WHAT ELSE DOES IT SAY?

07:22.773 --> 07:24.024
WHAT ELSE
ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

07:24.024 --> 07:26.827
I JUST FEEL LIKE
THERE'S MORE TO THE STORY.

07:26.827 --> 07:28.158
IT'S ALL RIGHT HERE.

07:28.158 --> 07:30.030
FBI TENDS
TO BE PRETTY THOROUGH.

07:30.030 --> 07:33.033
[ SIGHS ] I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S JUST...

07:33.033 --> 07:34.745
IT'S A GUT INSTINCT,
NOLAN.

07:34.745 --> 07:35.996
I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT.

07:35.996 --> 07:37.668
WELL, MAYBE
HIS INTERVIEW TONIGHT WILL.

07:37.668 --> 07:39.129
IF HE'S HIDING SOMETHING
FROM THE FBI,

07:39.129 --> 07:40.631
HE'S NOT GONNA ANNOUNCE IT
TO THE WHOLE WORLD

07:40.631 --> 07:43.133
ON LIVE TELEVISION.

07:43.133 --> 07:47.508
EMS [SIGHS]
I RESPECT YOUR INSTINCT,

07:47.508 --> 07:50.350
BUT I THINK YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR AN EASIER ANSWER.

07:50.350 --> 07:53.554
'CAUSE THE TRUTH
IS ANYTHING BUT.

07:54.935 --> 07:56.597
IT'S HARD TO ACCEPT
THAT THIS HAPPENED

07:56.597 --> 07:58.599
TO SOMEONE THAT WE LOVED.

08:00.100 --> 08:01.151
BUT IT DID.

08:04.985 --> 08:07.487
SO, I ASSUME YOU SAW
PAGE SIX.

08:07.487 --> 08:08.869
OH, NO.
WHAT HAVE I DONE NOW?

08:08.869 --> 08:10.160
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:10.160 --> 08:13.453
THEY RAN A STORY ON YOU
AND ONE MISS LOUISE ELLIS.

08:13.453 --> 08:14.745
THEY RAN A WHAT?

08:14.745 --> 08:17.117
Quite the little sexpot,
isn't she?

08:17.117 --> 08:18.118
OH, GOD.

08:18.118 --> 08:20.080
No, it's good news.

08:20.080 --> 08:22.122
"Louise Ellis lands
in New York

08:22.122 --> 08:25.335
AND HIRES DANIEL GRAYSON
TO MANAGE HER MILLIONS."

08:25.335 --> 08:27.127
SEEMS LIKE YOU'RE BACK
IN THE GAME, BIG BOY.

08:29.590 --> 08:32.011
HOW'S, UH, HOW'S THE INTERVIEW
COMING TOGETHER?

08:32.011 --> 08:33.594
RAPIDLY.

08:33.594 --> 08:35.846
I HAVE ONE LAST CALL
TO MAKE TO OUR STATION
DIRECTOR IN TOKYO,

08:35.846 --> 08:37.638
AND THEN I CAN FINALLY
CATCH MY BREATH.

08:37.638 --> 08:39.019
Join me
for some tennis later?

08:39.019 --> 08:40.140
NO, I CAN'T.

08:40.140 --> 08:43.143
A REALTOR'S SHOWING ME
SOME OFFICE SPACES.

08:43.143 --> 08:45.235
THANKS TO YOUR BEACH-HOUSE
P.R. STUNT,

08:45.235 --> 08:46.987
MY PHONE'S BEEN RINGING
OFF THE HOOK.

08:46.987 --> 08:50.030
WHEN IT RAINS.
 à BIENTôT.

08:50.030 --> 08:51.702
CIAO.

08:53.113 --> 08:54.284
Victoria:
WAS THAT MARGAUX?

08:54.284 --> 08:56.156
OH, MY GOD.

08:56.156 --> 08:58.038
HOW THE HELL
DID YOU GET IN HERE?

08:58.038 --> 08:59.499
I'M YOUR MOTHER --

08:59.499 --> 09:04.084
A FACT THAT YOU DON'T RESPECT,
BUT YOUR DOORMAN DOES.

09:04.084 --> 09:06.126
I WAS HOPING
TO CATCH MARGAUX HERE.

09:06.126 --> 09:07.377
IT'S URGENT.

09:07.377 --> 09:10.090
SO IS YOUR BOYFRIEND'S INTERVIEW
THAT SHE'S BUSY SETTING UP.

09:10.090 --> 09:13.303
YES, WELL,
IT'S RELATED.

09:13.303 --> 09:15.305
I'M WORRIED.

09:15.305 --> 09:17.938
DAVID HAS BEEN ACTING
VERY STRANGE WITH ME LATELY,

09:17.938 --> 09:19.269
AND I --

09:20.440 --> 09:22.062
WHAT IS THIS?

09:26.446 --> 09:28.068
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH LOUISE ELLIS?

09:28.068 --> 09:29.279
WHAT'S IT TO YOU?

09:29.279 --> 09:32.572
THIS GIRL
IS MENTALLY IMBALANCED.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.194
SO SHE'S A FRIEND OF YOURS.

09:34.194 --> 09:35.616
I AM SERIOUS, DANIEL.

09:35.616 --> 09:37.658
[ NEWSPAPER THUDS ]

09:39.409 --> 09:41.251
WHEN I DISAPPEARED
AFTER PASCAL'S DEATH,

09:41.251 --> 09:43.043
I'D FALLEN APART,
AND I NEEDED HELP,

09:43.043 --> 09:47.467
SO I CHECKED IN
TO A PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL.

09:49.089 --> 09:51.551
WHOA. [ CHUCKLES ]
HOLD ON A SECOND.

09:53.013 --> 09:55.595
THAT'S WHERE YOU WERE
ALL THAT TIME?

09:55.595 --> 09:57.267
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

09:57.267 --> 10:00.390
I COULDN'T BEAR FOR YOU
TO SEE MY LIFE IN SHAMBLES.

10:01.982 --> 10:04.434
IN THERE,
LOUISE WAS MY ROOMMATE.

10:04.434 --> 10:06.356
AND NOW THAT
SHE'S HIRED YOU,

10:06.356 --> 10:08.438
I'M HIGHLY SUSPECT
OF HER INTENTIONS.

10:08.438 --> 10:10.651
LOOK, EVEN IF LOUISE
ISN'T STABLE,

10:10.651 --> 10:12.322
HER BANK ACCOUNTS
CERTAINLY ARE.

10:12.322 --> 10:14.444
BELIEVE ME.
I CAN HANDLE HER.

10:14.444 --> 10:17.658
YOU ONCE SAID THE EXACT
SAME THING ABOUT EMILY THORNE.

10:19.199 --> 10:21.161
[ SIGHS ]

10:32.462 --> 10:34.054
[ Dialing ]

10:51.031 --> 10:53.403
Man:
I HATE TO END ON A LOW NOTE,

10:53.403 --> 10:57.237
BUT FOR THOSE WHO KNEW
FORMER OFFICER JIM MOSTROWSKI,

10:57.237 --> 10:59.159
JUST GOT NEWS HE PASSED AWAY.

10:59.159 --> 11:00.580
HEART ATTACK.

11:00.580 --> 11:02.242
THERE IS A WAKE
AT HIS HOUSE TONIGHT.

11:02.242 --> 11:04.875
YOU STOP BY IF YOU CAN
TO PAY YOUR RESPECTS.

11:04.875 --> 11:07.627
THAT'S IT. STAY SAFE.

11:07.627 --> 11:09.129
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

11:09.129 --> 11:10.130
READY WHEN YOU ARE.

11:10.130 --> 11:11.171
YEAH, GIVE ME A SEC.

11:11.171 --> 11:13.383
HEY, WILLARD, HOLD UP.

11:13.383 --> 11:15.756
THAT'S THE SAME MOSTROWSKI
THAT MOVED UP

11:15.756 --> 11:16.797
TO FULTON CORRECTIONAL,
ISN'T IT?

11:18.178 --> 11:19.679
IS ANYONE LOOKING
INTO HIS DEATH?

11:19.679 --> 11:20.761
CONSIDERING --

11:20.761 --> 11:22.102
IS THIS GOING
WHERE I THINK IT'S GOING?

11:22.102 --> 11:23.103
NO, I'M JUST SAYING,

11:23.103 --> 11:24.104
ACCORDING TO THAT CASE FILE,

11:24.104 --> 11:25.395
MOSTROWSKI BEAT UP
CONRAD GRAYSON

11:25.395 --> 11:26.727
RIGHT BEFORE GRAYSON
WAS MURDERED.

11:26.727 --> 11:28.809
THE CHIEF TOLD YOU
TO DROP THIS.

11:28.809 --> 11:29.940
BESIDES, MO WAS CLEARED.

11:29.940 --> 11:31.151
YEAH, BUT NOW THAT
HE'S SHOWING UP DEAD --

11:31.151 --> 11:32.272
YEAH,
FROM A HEART ATTACK.

11:32.272 --> 11:34.314
WATCH YOUR PARTNER,
PORTER.

11:34.314 --> 11:36.817
LAST WEEK, HE'D HAVE GIVEN HIS
LEFT NUT TO PIN THIS ON YOU.

11:41.531 --> 11:43.824
JACK [STAMMERS]

11:45.455 --> 11:48.328
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES,
ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

11:48.328 --> 11:50.130
JACK, WAIT UP!

11:50.130 --> 11:51.291
PORTER,
I KNOW YOU'RE PISSED.

11:51.291 --> 11:52.542
JUST GIVE ME A SECOND
TO EXPLAIN.

11:52.542 --> 11:53.754
WHAT THE HELL IS WRONG
WITH YOU?

11:53.754 --> 11:55.886
WHEN DID YOU START TELLING
EVERYONE AT THE STATION

11:55.886 --> 11:57.097
YOU THOUGHT I WAS
A MURDERER?

11:57.097 --> 11:59.179
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'RE UNBELIEVABLE.

11:59.179 --> 12:00.640
LOOK, COME ON.

12:00.640 --> 12:02.342
I DROPPED IT SOON AS I FOUND OUT
THAT YOU HAD AN ALIBI.

12:02.342 --> 12:04.935
[ Chuckling ] OH, OKAY.
WELL, THAT MAKES ME FEEL BETTER.

12:04.935 --> 12:06.056
LOOK, ALL I'VE EVER WANTED

12:06.056 --> 12:07.607
WAS TO BECOME
A DETECTIVE, ALL RIGHT?

12:07.607 --> 12:09.940
SOLVING A COLD CASE LIKE THIS --
THAT WOULD DO THAT FOR ME.

12:09.940 --> 12:12.402
DO YOU REALLY WANT
TO MAKE YOUR CAREER THIS WAY?

12:12.402 --> 12:14.194
WHOEVER KILLED CONRAD
DESERVES A MEDAL.

12:14.194 --> 12:15.615
AND YOU WONDER WHY
I SUSPECTED YOU.

12:15.615 --> 12:17.027
COME ON.

12:17.027 --> 12:19.279
AFTER EVERYTHING YOU SAID
HE DID TO YOU, RIGHT --

12:19.279 --> 12:20.660
YOUR WIFE, YOUR BROTHER --

12:20.660 --> 12:22.742
YOU TELLING ME THE THOUGHT
OF KILLING THAT BASTARD

12:22.742 --> 12:24.414
NEVER CROSSED YOUR MIND?

12:24.414 --> 12:27.707
EVEN IF IT HAD,
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

12:27.707 --> 12:29.579
YOU'RE A BEAT COP.
YOU'RE NOT A DETECTIVE.

12:29.579 --> 12:31.461
AND THE CHIEF TOLD YOU
TO DROP THIS,

12:31.461 --> 12:34.504
SO IF YOU DON'T, IT REFLECTS
BADLY ON ME, YOUR PARTNER.

12:34.504 --> 12:37.587
SO STOP BEING A PAIN IN THE ASS
AND FIND A NEW HOBBY

12:37.587 --> 12:39.469
BEFORE YOU SCREW
THIS JOB UP FOR BOTH OF US.

12:39.469 --> 12:41.051
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

12:41.051 --> 12:43.183
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

12:43.183 --> 12:45.145
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

12:54.154 --> 12:56.026
WHERE IS HE?

13:02.993 --> 13:05.365
HIS NECK'S BROKEN.

13:05.365 --> 13:06.827
WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL
THE POLICE?

13:06.827 --> 13:08.118
I WAS GOING TO.

13:08.118 --> 13:09.499
I WAS --
I WAS DIALING THEM,

13:09.499 --> 13:12.542
BUT THEN I-I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO MAKE OF ALL THIS.

13:12.542 --> 13:14.875
[ TRAIN HORN BLARING
IN DISTANCE ]

13:14.875 --> 13:16.336
HE CALLED ME "BAIT."

13:16.336 --> 13:18.919
HE WAS USING ME
TO GET TO OUR FATHER.

13:18.919 --> 13:20.090
BUT WHY?

13:20.090 --> 13:21.721
WHY WOULD ANYONE WANT
TO HURT HIM?

13:25.055 --> 13:29.429
SAME MAKE AND MODEL THAT TRIED
TO RUN DOWN DAVID THE OTHER DAY.

13:31.641 --> 13:33.313
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

13:33.313 --> 13:36.146
OH, GOD. I SHOULD HAVE
JUST CALLED THE POLICE.

13:36.146 --> 13:37.647
BUT I CALLED YOU
AS A LAST RESORT,

13:37.647 --> 13:39.319
BUT [EXHALES SHARPLY]
HE'S OUR DAD,

13:39.319 --> 13:41.361
AND I THOUGHT AFTER EVERYTHING
YOU'D DONE TO ME, TO OUR FAMILY,

13:41.361 --> 13:42.532
I THOUGHT MAYBE
YOU COULD HELP.

13:42.532 --> 13:44.494
BASED ON THIS FILE,
IT LOOKS HE WAS ONE

13:44.494 --> 13:46.326
OF THE REMAINING
FLIGHT 197 FANATICS

13:46.326 --> 13:48.038
WHO STILL DOUBTED
DAVID'S INNOCENCE.

13:48.038 --> 13:50.500
THIS GUY DESERVED
WHAT HE GOT.

13:50.500 --> 13:51.711
WHAT DRUGS WERE YOU DOING?

13:51.711 --> 13:54.414
WE WERE JUST DRINKING,
MAYBE DOING A LITTLE COKE.

13:54.414 --> 13:56.126
HE OFFERED ME HEROIN,
BUT I DON'T --

13:56.126 --> 13:58.718
PERFECT.
WE'RE GONNA NEED IT.

14:03.093 --> 14:05.055
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

14:15.025 --> 14:18.148
I DON'T THINK I WILL EVER GET
USED TO SEEING YOU AT MY DOOR.

14:18.148 --> 14:19.529
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:19.529 --> 14:21.281
UH, COME IN.
 THANK YOU.

14:23.944 --> 14:26.036
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT WHAT YOU TOLD ME --

14:26.036 --> 14:28.158
THAT I SHOULDN'T BE SO QUICK
TO TRUST JUST ANYONE.

14:28.158 --> 14:30.250
YOU MEANT VICTORIA,
RIGHT?

14:30.250 --> 14:31.451
I [SIGHS]

14:31.451 --> 14:33.253
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL
ABOUT THE GRAYSONS,

14:33.253 --> 14:35.665
HOW YOU'VE ALWAYS FELT.

14:35.665 --> 14:37.337
AND NOW I KNOW NOW WHAT THEY DID
TO YOU AND YOUR COMPANY.

14:37.337 --> 14:38.758
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

14:38.758 --> 14:40.210
I WISH COULD HAVE BEEN
THERE FOR YOU, NOLAN,

14:40.210 --> 14:42.382
THE WAY YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN
THERE FOR ME.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.965
WHICH IS WHY,
IF YOU CAN, I WOULD --

14:44.965 --> 14:47.137
I WOULD LIKE IT IF YOU CAME
TO THE INTERVIEW TONIGHT.

14:47.137 --> 14:51.391
I NEED SOMEONE ON MY SIDE
IN CASE I GET CORNERED.

14:51.391 --> 14:53.183
THEN I'LL BE THERE.

14:53.183 --> 14:55.105
[ SIGHS ]

14:55.105 --> 14:57.067
I'M PROUD OF YOU, NOLAN.

14:57.067 --> 15:00.280
ALL YOUR HARD WORK --
IT'S PAID OFF IN SPADES.

15:00.280 --> 15:03.733
I WOULDN'T HAVE
ANY OF THIS

15:03.733 --> 15:06.156
IF YOU HADN'T BELIEVED IN ME
WAY BACK WHEN.

15:07.907 --> 15:09.329
BUT I DID.

15:13.453 --> 15:15.335
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

15:15.335 --> 15:17.167
[ SOFT JAZZ PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

15:32.052 --> 15:34.224
VICTORIA?

15:34.224 --> 15:35.935
OH, THANKS SO MUCH
FOR REACHING OUT TO ME.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.687
OH!
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

15:37.687 --> 15:39.269
I READ THE BLURB
IN PAGE SIX.

15:39.269 --> 15:41.821
HOW EXCITING -- YOU AND MY SON
WORKING TOGETHER.

15:41.821 --> 15:43.403
I DID IT FOR YOU,
YOU KNOW.

15:43.403 --> 15:46.026
I KNEW DANIEL
NEEDED BUSINESS,

15:46.026 --> 15:49.369
AND, WELL, I JUST WANTED
TO REPAY YOU

15:49.369 --> 15:51.031
FOR THE KINDNESS
YOU SHOWED ME AT CLAREMONT.

15:51.031 --> 15:53.873
NOW, I KNOW OUR TIME THERE
WAS BRIEF,

15:53.873 --> 15:57.577
BUT, WELL, LIFE IS JUST
A SERIES OF MOMENTS.

15:59.209 --> 16:01.001
I WAS ABOUT TO SAY
THE VERY SAME THING.

16:01.001 --> 16:04.044
OH, LOUISE,
I'M SO HAPPY WE MET.

16:04.044 --> 16:09.179
YOU'VE BEEN A BETTER CHILD TO ME
THAN MY OWN BLOOD, LOUISE.

16:09.179 --> 16:10.640
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

16:10.640 --> 16:12.512
MY OWN BLOOD.

16:15.855 --> 16:17.227
[ SIGHS ]

16:19.149 --> 16:21.101
[ SIGHS ]

16:24.404 --> 16:26.316
VICTORIA.

16:26.316 --> 16:29.069
[ SIGHS ] THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR REACHING OUT TO ME.

16:29.069 --> 16:31.031
PLEASE.

16:31.031 --> 16:33.033
MS. GRAYSON,
YOUR TABLE IS READY.

16:33.033 --> 16:35.075
HOW PERFECT. I'M FAMISHED.

16:35.075 --> 16:37.707
ACTUALLY, MY LUNCH DATE
IS WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

16:37.707 --> 16:41.211
I'M RATHER SHORT ON TIME,
BUT WE'RE OVERDUE FOR A CHAT.

16:43.713 --> 16:45.125
I HEAR YOU'LL BE WORKING
WITH MY SON.

16:45.125 --> 16:46.466
MM.

16:46.466 --> 16:48.508
NOW, OF ALL THE FINANCIAL
ADVISERS IN MANHATTAN,

16:48.508 --> 16:50.510
HOW DID THAT HAPPEN?

16:50.510 --> 16:52.802
WELL, IT WAS PRACTICALLY
YOUR IDEA.

16:52.802 --> 16:54.684
I NEVER MENTIONED DANIEL
TO YOU.

16:54.684 --> 16:56.015
WELL, NO, BUT YOU DID SAY

16:56.015 --> 16:58.768
YOUR FAMILY WAS STRUGGLING
WITH FINANCES.

16:58.768 --> 17:00.560
IF THIS IS BECAUSE I LEFT YOU
AT CLAREMONT --

17:00.560 --> 17:02.192
VICTORIA, I TOLD YOU.

17:02.192 --> 17:04.144
I DON'T BLAME YOU FOR THAT.

17:04.144 --> 17:06.146
I SIMPLY JUST WANT
TO REPAY THE KINDNESS

17:06.146 --> 17:08.407
YOU SHOWED ME IN THERE.

17:08.407 --> 17:10.990
YOU WERE LIKE A MOTHER
TO ME.

17:10.990 --> 17:13.653
WE WERE ROOMMATES
FOR A DAY.

17:13.653 --> 17:16.246
WELL, SURE, BUT...

17:17.367 --> 17:20.250
...LIFE IS JUST A SERIES
OF MOMENTS.

17:21.830 --> 17:23.542
WHATEVER DOES THAT MEAN?

17:23.542 --> 17:26.256
LOUISE, I DON'T WISH
TO SOUND UNGRATEFUL,

17:26.256 --> 17:28.088
BUT IF YOUR INTENTIONS
TOWARD MY SON

17:28.088 --> 17:29.669
ARE ANYTHING
OTHER THAN HONEST,

17:29.669 --> 17:32.972
WELL, I'M SURE YOU KNOW
HOW TERRIFYING

17:32.972 --> 17:35.014
A MOTHER'S LOVE
FOR HER CHILDREN CAN BE.

17:35.014 --> 17:37.097
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

17:37.097 --> 17:38.017
DO I EVER.

17:40.480 --> 17:42.732
VICTORIA, WAIT.

17:42.732 --> 17:45.445
[ SIGHS ] WHEN CAN WE SEE
EACH OTHER AGAIN?

17:45.445 --> 17:48.027
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

18:05.125 --> 18:06.166
AND WHAT'S THIS?

18:06.166 --> 18:07.337
IT'S A LIST OF QUESTIONS

18:07.337 --> 18:08.668
FOR THE INTERVIEWER TO ASK.

18:08.668 --> 18:11.421
OH, MY NEWS DIVISION
HAS ALREADY HANDLED THIS.

18:11.421 --> 18:14.974
THEN I NEED YOUR ASSURANCE
THAT IF ANYTHING GOES WRONG,

18:14.974 --> 18:16.476
YOU'LL CUT THE LIVE FEED.

18:16.476 --> 18:20.430
AND WHAT EXACTLY DO YOU EXPECT
TO GO WRONG, VICTORIA?

18:21.931 --> 18:25.064
OR DO WE HAVE AN EVEN BIGGER
STORY THAN I THOUGHT?

18:25.064 --> 18:28.278
LISTEN, I'M HAPPY FOR YOU
TO BE THERE,

18:28.278 --> 18:31.731
BUT I WON'T TOLERATE
ANY INTERFERENCE.

18:31.731 --> 18:34.364
I'M PLANNING TO TELL NOLAN ROSS
THE SAME.

18:34.364 --> 18:35.365
[ SCOFFS ]

18:35.365 --> 18:37.076
WHAT DOES NOLAN HAVE TO DO
WITH THIS?

18:37.076 --> 18:39.038
DAVID REQUESTED
HIS PRESENCE.

18:42.081 --> 18:44.244
[ DRAWER CLOSES ]
 LET'S GO THROUGH THIS
AGAIN.

18:44.244 --> 18:45.455
HE SHOT UP.

18:45.455 --> 18:47.006
SHORTLY AFTER REALIZING
HE TOOK TOO MUCH,

18:47.006 --> 18:50.129
HE STUMBLED OVER HERE
IN AN ATTEMPT TO CALL 911.

18:50.129 --> 18:52.922
BEFORE HE COULD,
HE COLLAPSED,

18:52.922 --> 18:54.344
BREAKING HIS NECK
WHEN HE FELL.

18:54.344 --> 18:56.055
AM I MISSING ANYTHING?

18:56.055 --> 18:57.557
I CUT HIM WITH THE BOTTLE.

18:57.557 --> 18:59.138
NO.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.931
WHEN HE FELL,
HE SWIPED THE COUNTER.

19:01.931 --> 19:05.935
BOTTLE BROKE.
CUT HIS HAND.

19:05.935 --> 19:08.067
[ SIGHS ]

19:08.067 --> 19:09.979
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHAT IT'S LIKE
BEING YOU.

19:09.979 --> 19:11.651
I MEAN, I KNOW THIS WAS
ALL MY FAULT,

19:11.651 --> 19:13.032
BUT IT WAS
JUST A MISTAKE.

19:13.032 --> 19:14.574
I'M NOT
A COLD-BLOODED KILLER.

19:14.574 --> 19:17.036
I'VE NEVER KILLED ANYONE,
CHARLOTTE.

19:17.036 --> 19:19.078
I KNOW YOU HATE ME
FOR THE THINGS THAT I'VE DONE,

19:19.078 --> 19:22.202
BUT I'VE NEVER DONE THAT.

19:22.202 --> 19:26.125
SADLY, ERASING EVERY TRACE
OF MYSELF IS MY EXPERTISE.

19:26.125 --> 19:27.917
AS YOUR MOTHER POINTED OUT,

19:27.917 --> 19:29.789
IT'S SOMETHING I'VE DONE
ALL TOO WELL,

19:29.789 --> 19:32.882
WHICH IS WHY I CAN'T SEE
OUR FATHER YET.

19:34.634 --> 19:37.677
I THINK
YOU'RE JUST ASHAMED.
 [ LIGHTER CLICKS ]

19:37.677 --> 19:39.429
GOD FORBID HE SEES
WHAT YOU'VE BECOME.

19:42.141 --> 19:44.013
YOU KNOW,
FOR A WHILE NOW,

19:44.013 --> 19:45.565
I'VE GIVEN YOU
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT

19:45.565 --> 19:47.397
BECAUSE YOUR PARENTS
DID YOU NO FAVORS

19:47.397 --> 19:49.108
BY PROTECTING YOU
WITH LIES.

19:49.108 --> 19:52.191
BUT YOU'RE TOO OLD FOR EXCUSES,
CHARLOTTE.

19:52.191 --> 19:54.984
IT'S TIME YOU OWN
YOUR BAD CHOICES.

19:54.984 --> 19:57.527
THIS COULD EASILY HAVE BEEN
YOU LYING THERE.

19:57.527 --> 19:59.989
YOU ONLY CALLED ME

19:59.989 --> 20:02.372
BECAUSE YOU WANTED SOMEONE
TO COME AND SAVE YOU.

20:02.372 --> 20:04.704
BUT I CAN'T DO THAT.

20:04.704 --> 20:07.247
YOU'VE HIT ROCK BOTTOM.

20:08.788 --> 20:11.711
ONLY YOU CAN
PULL YOURSELF OUT.

20:18.838 --> 20:21.721
AREN'T THEY GONNA KNOW THAT
HE DIED BEFORE HE SHOT UP?

20:21.721 --> 20:22.802
IT'S TRUE.

20:22.802 --> 20:27.557
DRUGS CAN'T CIRCULATE
ONCE THE HEART STOPS.

20:27.557 --> 20:31.190
BUT YOU DON'T NEED TO BE ALIVE
TO CIRCULATE YOUR BLOOD.

20:37.407 --> 20:38.698
AIDEN DIED OF AN OVERDOSE.

20:38.698 --> 20:41.070
ISN'T THAT WHAT
THE CORONER SAID?

20:43.162 --> 20:45.705
BUT HE DIDN'T, DID HE?

20:45.705 --> 20:48.077
AND YOU SAID YOU'D NEVER
KILLED ANYONE.

20:51.130 --> 20:52.081
I HAVEN'T.

20:53.132 --> 20:55.174
YOUR MOTHER KILLED HIM.

21:11.060 --> 21:12.442
WHOO!

21:12.442 --> 21:13.563
LOOKING GOOD OUT THERE.

21:13.563 --> 21:15.024
HEY!

21:15.024 --> 21:16.025
AND YOUR SWING AIN'T BAD,
EITHER.

21:16.025 --> 21:17.317
OH, A FEW MORE WEEKS
OF PRACTICE,

21:17.317 --> 21:19.569
AND I'LL BE ABLE TO WHIP
 TON DERRIèRE.

21:19.569 --> 21:21.280
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:21.280 --> 21:22.992
OH, HI, DANIEL.

21:22.992 --> 21:24.243
OH!
WHAT A SMALL WORLD.

21:24.243 --> 21:27.286
MY PARTNER DIDN'T SHOW,
AND, LUCKY FOR ME,

21:27.286 --> 21:29.579
YOUR NEW CLIENT JUST JOINED
THE CLUB.

21:29.579 --> 21:31.000
I CAN SEE THAT.

21:31.000 --> 21:33.373
YOU NEVER TOLD ME
HOW COMPETITIVE THIS ONE IS.

21:33.373 --> 21:36.045
THAT'S FUNNY -- I THOUGHT
I'D TOLD YOU ALL ABOUT MARGAUX.

21:37.216 --> 21:39.178
I'M SURPRISED
TO SEE YOU HERE.

21:39.178 --> 21:40.760
I -- UH, YOU KNOW,
I HAD --

21:40.760 --> 21:42.722
REALTOR WAS SHOWING ME SOME
OFFICE SPACE AROUND THE CORNER.

21:42.722 --> 21:44.093
I THOUGHT I'D STOP BY

21:44.093 --> 21:46.476
AND WISH YOU LUCK
FOR THE INTERVIEW TONIGHT.

21:46.476 --> 21:48.057
OH, YEAH.
I MUST BE GOING.

21:48.057 --> 21:50.770
I'M MEETING THE CREW EARLY
TO GO OVER DETAILS.

21:50.770 --> 21:52.562
A PLEASURE, LOUISE.

21:52.562 --> 21:54.484
NEXT TIME,
WINNER BUYS LUNCH?

21:54.484 --> 21:56.235
DEAL.

21:56.235 --> 21:58.067
BYE.
 BYE.

21:58.067 --> 22:00.570
Louise:
THAT LITTLE ACCENT OF HERS

22:00.570 --> 22:04.073
IS ABOUT THE CUTEST THING
I'VE EVER HEARD.

22:04.073 --> 22:05.114
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

22:05.114 --> 22:07.076
DIDN'T KNOW I PLAYED TENNIS,
DID YOU?

22:07.076 --> 22:09.208
HUNDREDS OF MEMBERS
AT THIS CLUB,

22:09.208 --> 22:11.501
AND YOU JUST HAPPEN TO BUDDY UP
WITH MY GIRLFRIEND?

22:11.501 --> 22:13.332
THAT'S QUITE A COINCIDENCE,
WOULDN'T YOU SAY?

22:13.332 --> 22:15.455
A COMPLETELY INNOCENT ONE.

22:15.455 --> 22:19.048
I JUST SIGNED UP TO BE A SUB,
AND SHE ASKED ME TO PLAY.

22:19.048 --> 22:21.841
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
YOU KNEW MY MOTHER FROM
A PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL?

22:24.594 --> 22:27.226
WELL, I DIDN'T THINK YOUR MOTHER
WOULD WANT ME TO SHARE THAT.

22:27.226 --> 22:28.267
COME ON.

22:28.267 --> 22:30.099
PEOPLE LOOK AT YOU DIFFERENTLY
WHEN THEY KNOW.

22:30.099 --> 22:32.682
KIND OF LIKE THE WAY
YOU'RE LOOKING AT ME RIGHT NOW.

22:35.314 --> 22:37.236
LOOK, I'M SORRY
IF I SEEM A LITTLE PARANOID.

22:37.236 --> 22:39.068
IT JUST WOULDN'T BE
THE FIRST TIME

22:39.068 --> 22:41.651
I'D BEEN TARGETED BY SOMEONE
WITH A HIDDEN AGENDA.

22:41.651 --> 22:45.154
OH, QUIT BEING SUCH A WORRYWART,
SUGAR.

22:45.154 --> 22:47.617
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH YOU.

22:54.874 --> 22:57.627
Woman: ALL RIGHT,
THREE MINUTES TO AIR, EVERYONE.

22:57.627 --> 22:59.839
THREE MINUTES.

23:03.002 --> 23:04.634
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:04.634 --> 23:07.056
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

23:07.056 --> 23:09.429
UH, POOR TIMING, EMS.
CAN'T TALK RIGHT NOW.

23:09.429 --> 23:11.010
EMILY:
I'm upstate at the silo.

23:11.010 --> 23:12.181
MY HUNCH WAS RIGHT, NOLAN.

23:12.181 --> 23:14.393
THERE'S MORE TO MY FATHER'S
STORY THAN HE'S ADMITTING.

23:14.393 --> 23:16.516
I HAVE A PHOTO OF HIM
IN PUBLIC.

23:16.516 --> 23:18.858
LIKE I SAID,
NOT A GOOD TIME.

23:18.858 --> 23:20.229
He's in some kind of
town square.

23:20.229 --> 23:22.862
THERE'S A BANK SIGN BEHIND HIM
LISTING THE DATE AS MARCH 15th,

23:22.862 --> 23:24.363
BUT THAT DOESN'T MATCH UP
TO HIS STORY

23:24.363 --> 23:26.195
THAT HE'S BEEN IMPRISONED
UNTIL LAST WEEK.

23:26.195 --> 23:27.236
AND FOR ALL YOU KNOW,

23:27.236 --> 23:29.579
IT WAS PHOTOSHOPPED BY SOMEONE
TRYING TO MAKE TROUBLE.

23:29.579 --> 23:30.990
COPS STILL HAVE THIS PLACE
ON LOCKDOWN.

23:30.990 --> 23:33.082
I NEED YOU TO HACK
INTO THEIR RADIO FREQUENCIES --

23:33.082 --> 23:35.585
HAVE DISPATCH DRAW THEM OUT
WITH AN EMERGENCY.

23:35.585 --> 23:36.996
[ SIGHS ]

23:36.996 --> 23:39.128
I'M DONE
INVESTIGATING HIM, EMS.

23:39.128 --> 23:41.090
IT'S TIME TO COME TO TERMS
WITH THE TRUTH

23:41.090 --> 23:42.421
INSTEAD OF MAKING UP
YOUR OWN.

23:42.421 --> 23:44.003
I'M NOT MAKING ANYTHING UP,
NOLAN,

23:44.003 --> 23:45.304
AND I DON'T UNDERSTAND

23:45.304 --> 23:46.636
WHY YOU'RE SO UNWILLING
TO DIG DEEPER.

23:46.636 --> 23:49.679
BECAUSE DAVID HAS BEEN
THROUGH ENOUGH.

23:49.679 --> 23:54.183
HE'S ABOUT TO GO ON LIVE TV,
AND...HE NEEDS MY SUPPORT.

23:56.556 --> 23:58.057
WAIT.
ARE YOU THERE WITH HIM?

23:58.057 --> 24:00.520
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE TOO AFRAID
TO RECONNECT WITH HIM

24:00.520 --> 24:02.562
DOESN'T MEAN I HAVE TO BE.

24:09.989 --> 24:12.622
AH! [ CHUCKLES ]

24:12.622 --> 24:14.914
JUST, UH, PLAYING HARDBALL
WITH A BUSINESS PARTNER.

24:14.914 --> 24:16.415
AH.
SAME, OLD NOLAN ROSS.

24:16.415 --> 24:18.748
NolCorp MAY BE A THING
OF THE PAST,

24:18.748 --> 24:20.540
BUT THE NEW COMPANY IS PROBABLY
RIGHT AROUND THE CORNER.

24:20.540 --> 24:22.712
I DO HAVE A FEW THINGS
PERCOLATING.

24:22.712 --> 24:23.713
NO DOUBT.

24:23.713 --> 24:25.344
DAVID, WE NEED YOU TO TAKE
YOUR SEAT.

24:26.506 --> 24:28.217
GLAD YOU CAME.
IT MEANS A LOT.

24:28.217 --> 24:30.219
THANKS.

24:31.931 --> 24:35.224
YOU TWO SEEM RATHER CLOSE
AS OF LATE.

24:35.224 --> 24:37.687
UM, WE'VE ALWAYS BEEN CLOSE,
VICTORIA.

24:37.687 --> 24:39.899
EVEN WHEN YOU LEFT HIM
TO ROT IN PRISON,

24:39.899 --> 24:41.190
I WAS STILL THERE FOR HIM.

24:41.190 --> 24:43.813
SEE, YOU MAY BE ABLE TO KEEP
DAVID AWAY FROM EMILY,

24:43.813 --> 24:46.906
BUT THAT'S OBVIOUSLY
NOT GONNA WORK WITH ME.

24:46.906 --> 24:48.948
OH, WELL, I'M NOT TRYING
TO KEEP HIM FROM ANYONE.

24:48.948 --> 24:50.199
[ SIGHS ]

24:50.199 --> 24:53.162
I SIMPLY DON'T WANT HIM TO SAY
SOMETHING HE MIGHT REGRET.

24:53.162 --> 24:54.534
LIKE WHAT?

24:54.534 --> 24:56.245
WHAT, ARE YOU AFRAID
I TOLD MY NEW FRIEND

24:56.245 --> 24:57.997
WHAT A WRETCHED WOMAN
YOU REALLY ARE?

24:57.997 --> 25:00.119
UH, YOU TWO,
YOU CAN TAKE YOUR PLACES.

25:00.119 --> 25:01.711
WE'RE STARTING.

25:01.711 --> 25:06.045
OH, I JUST LOVE LIVE TV.

25:06.045 --> 25:07.547
YOU NEVER KNOW
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

25:07.547 --> 25:08.758
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:08.758 --> 25:11.340
Woman: OKAY, WE ARE LIVE
IN 30 SECONDS, PEOPLE.

25:11.340 --> 25:14.223
THERE.
YOU'RE ALL SET.

25:18.057 --> 25:23.563
No matter what happens,
I will always be on your side.

25:23.563 --> 25:24.814
15 SECONDS.

25:24.814 --> 25:28.197
MRS. GRAYSON, WE'RE GONNA
NEED YOU TO MOVE, PLEASE.

25:30.650 --> 25:33.613
QUIET, EVERYONE.
CALL IT.

25:33.613 --> 25:36.786
OKAY, IN 5, 4, 3...

25:38.708 --> 25:40.079
Interviewer: GOOD EVENING.

25:40.079 --> 25:41.210
WE'RE HERE TONIGHT TO EXPLORE

25:41.210 --> 25:43.372
ONE OF THE MOST CONTROVERSIAL
STORIES OF OUR TIME.

25:43.372 --> 25:45.254
DAVID CLARKE, WELCOME.

25:51.010 --> 25:53.172
THAT PARTNER OF YOURS
IS STILL AT IT.

25:53.172 --> 25:55.935
HASSLING MO'S GRIEVING DAUGHTER
WITH QUESTIONS.

25:55.935 --> 25:57.476
I GIVE HIM
TWO MORE MINUTES

25:57.476 --> 25:59.769
BEFORE SHE THROWS THAT DRINK
IN HIS FACE.

26:01.601 --> 26:04.483
SO, NO ANGER ISSUES
OR ANYTHING THAT --

26:04.483 --> 26:06.776
THAT MAY HAVE LED TO
AN ALTERCATION WITH
ONE OF THE INMATES?

26:06.776 --> 26:09.068
NOT THAT I KNOW OF.

26:09.068 --> 26:10.740
HI. WE HAVEN'T MET.
I'M JACK PORTER.

26:10.740 --> 26:12.401
I'M SO SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

26:12.401 --> 26:14.113
BEN AND I NEVER GOT TO WORK
WITH YOUR FATHER,

26:14.113 --> 26:15.154
BUT WE HEARD GREAT THINGS.

26:15.154 --> 26:17.406
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,
PARTNER?

26:17.406 --> 26:18.577
INDEED.

26:18.577 --> 26:19.789
YEAH.

26:19.789 --> 26:21.000
MY POP WOULD HAVE BEEN
REAL PLEASED

26:21.000 --> 26:23.122
THAT SO MANY GUYS FROM
THE PRECINCT SHOWED UP TODAY.

26:23.122 --> 26:24.664
YEAH, YOU KNOW,
DENISE WAS JUST TELLING ME

26:24.664 --> 26:26.045
HOW HER DAD WON BIG
IN ATLANTIC CITY,

26:26.045 --> 26:28.007
TOOK AN EARLY RETIREMENT.

26:28.007 --> 26:29.338
IT WAS FUNNY HOW NEWS LIKE THAT

26:29.338 --> 26:31.050
DIDN'T MAKE ITS WAY BACK
TO THE STATION, THOUGH, HUH?

26:31.050 --> 26:32.301
WELL, NOT REALLY,

26:32.301 --> 26:34.804
CONSIDERING HE HADN'T
WORKED THERE IN YEARS.

26:34.804 --> 26:36.926
POP WASN'T ONE TO BRAG.

26:36.926 --> 26:39.218
AND, BESIDES, HE WAS REAL BUSY
THE LAST FEW WEEKS

26:39.218 --> 26:40.850
TRYING TO SELL
THE HOUSE.

26:40.850 --> 26:42.101
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

26:42.101 --> 26:43.222
EXCUSE ME.

26:45.024 --> 26:46.896
COME ON. YOU TELL ME
THAT DOESN'T SOUND SUSPICIOUS,

26:46.896 --> 26:48.648
LIKE HE'S TRYING TO GET
OUT OF TOWN IN A HURRY.

26:48.648 --> 26:50.609
We're at the man's wake.
 EXACTLY.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.031
AND THERE MAY BE PEOPLE
IN THIS ROOM

26:52.031 --> 26:53.402
WHO HAVE ANSWERS
THAT I NEED.

26:53.402 --> 26:55.194
THAT MAY BE TRUE,
BUT IF YOU KEEP PURSUING THIS,

26:55.194 --> 26:57.156
I'M PUTTING IN
FOR A NEW PARTNER.

27:00.499 --> 27:02.041
[ SIGHS ]

27:07.707 --> 27:10.509
Interviewer: CONRAD GRAYSON
THEN IMPRISONS YOU

27:10.509 --> 27:13.302
IN THE BASEMENT OF A SILO
FOR 10 YEARS,

27:13.302 --> 27:16.886
CUT OFF FROM THE WORLD.

27:16.886 --> 27:18.137
WHAT WAS IT LIKE IN THERE?

27:18.137 --> 27:21.891
David:
UH, FILTHY, OPPRESSIVE.

27:21.891 --> 27:25.474
IT WAS INHUMAN,
IS WHAT IT WAS.

27:25.474 --> 27:28.527
I DRANK WATER FROM THE SAME
PLACE THAT I BATHED.

27:28.527 --> 27:29.899
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

27:29.899 --> 27:33.362
I SLEPT ON A SMALL COT --

27:33.362 --> 27:35.074
THAT IS,
WHEN I COULD SLEEP.

27:37.076 --> 27:42.451
I SPENT OVER 4,000 DAYS
OF MY LIFE DOWN THERE...

27:42.451 --> 27:46.045
YET TIME,
IT SEEMED TO STAND STILL.

27:46.045 --> 27:49.128
I NEEDED IT TO
SO THAT I COULD MAINTAIN HOPE.

27:49.128 --> 27:50.880
BUT IT WASN'T LIVING.

27:50.880 --> 27:53.172
IT WAS SURVIVAL.

28:01.350 --> 28:02.722
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

28:29.208 --> 28:31.540
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

28:31.540 --> 28:35.094
THE QUESTION ON ALL
OF OUR MINDS IS,

28:35.094 --> 28:36.295
HOW DID YOU NOT GIVE UP?

28:36.295 --> 28:37.797
[ SIGHS ]

28:37.797 --> 28:41.640
WELL, THERE WERE TIMES WHEN
I...THOUGHT ABOUT ENDING IT ALL.

28:41.640 --> 28:44.723
BUT THEN, THE PEOPLE
WHO WRONGED ME WOULD HAVE WON,

28:44.723 --> 28:47.346
AND I NEVER WOULD HAVE HAD
THE CHANCE

28:47.346 --> 28:49.018
TO SEE THE PEOPLE THAT I LOVED,

28:49.018 --> 28:53.022
ONE OF WHOM IS,
UH, HERE TODAY.

28:53.022 --> 28:55.614
NOLAN, COME JOIN ME.

29:02.031 --> 29:04.073
David's exhausted.

29:04.073 --> 29:06.125
This is too much for him.
We need to end this.

29:06.125 --> 29:07.166
THIS IS EXACTLY WHAT

29:07.166 --> 29:09.038
THE AUDIENCE WANTS TO HEAR,
VICTORIA.

29:09.038 --> 29:10.459
I KNOW I DO.

29:10.459 --> 29:13.923
Interviewer: ALL RIGHT,
WELL, IT'S PUBLIC KNOWLEDGE

29:13.923 --> 29:16.215
THAT MR. CLARKE
AND ENTREPRENEUR NOLAN ROSS

29:16.215 --> 29:18.257
WERE BUSINESS ASSOCIATES
YEARS AGO.

29:18.257 --> 29:20.139
MR. ROSS, WELCOME.

29:20.139 --> 29:22.641
UH, NOLAN WAS LIKE
THE SON I NEVER HAD.

29:22.641 --> 29:25.975
AND I KNEW HIS FIRST COMPANY
WOULD BE A SUCCESS, AND IT WAS.

29:25.975 --> 29:30.189
WELL, BECAUSE YOU HAD
THE COURAGE TO INVEST IN ME.

29:30.189 --> 29:32.691
AN INVESTMENT
THAT PAID OFF.

29:32.691 --> 29:34.523
I FIGURED
THE PROFITS WOULD PROVIDE

29:34.523 --> 29:37.606
A NICE NEST EGG
FOR MY DAUGHTER, AMANDA.

29:41.991 --> 29:43.492
SHE NEVER GOT THE MONEY,
DID SHE, NOLAN?

29:45.114 --> 29:47.997
OF COURSE SHE DID.
OF COURSE SHE DID.

29:47.997 --> 29:51.080
YOU LIED TO HER,
AND YOU LIED TO ME.

29:51.080 --> 29:52.912
AND YOU STOLE
HER INHERITANCE.

29:54.914 --> 29:57.176
UM [CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

29:57.176 --> 29:59.048
I GAVE HER ALL THE MONEY
THAT SHE WAS OWED.

29:59.048 --> 30:01.050
WHAT -- WHAT SHE CHOSE
TO DO WITH IT, I-I --

30:01.050 --> 30:02.471
I OBTAINED
HER FINANCIAL RECORDS.

30:02.471 --> 30:04.053
WHEN SHE TURNED 18,

30:04.053 --> 30:06.135
SHE WAS TO RECEIVE HUNDREDS
OF MILLIONS OF DOLLARS,

30:06.135 --> 30:10.229
BUT INSTEAD,
SHE ONLY GOT $100,000.

30:10.229 --> 30:12.231
[ SCOFFS ]

30:12.231 --> 30:14.934
THAT'S UH, QUITE A DISCREPANCY,
DON'T YOU THINK?

30:14.934 --> 30:17.026
David, please.
This is not the place.

30:17.026 --> 30:18.237
I TRUSTED YOU.

30:18.237 --> 30:19.989
I LEFT THE RESPONSIBILITY

30:19.989 --> 30:21.700
OF MY DAUGHTER'S FUTURE
IN YOUR HANDS.

30:21.700 --> 30:23.492
BUT WHILE YOU WERE OUT
BUYING CUSTOM CARS

30:23.492 --> 30:27.997
AND YOUR OWN PRIVATE ISLAND,
SHE WAS SCRAPING BY.

30:27.997 --> 30:29.288
[ SCOFFS ]

30:29.288 --> 30:31.871
SHE WORKED AS A STRIPPER,
FOR GOD'S SAKES.

30:33.162 --> 30:36.505
SHE DIED WITHOUT KNOWING
THAT YOU'D BETRAYED HER,

30:36.505 --> 30:38.547
THAT YOU'D BETRAYED ME.

30:38.547 --> 30:41.720
AND FOR THAT,
I WILL NEVER FORGIVE YOU.

30:43.883 --> 30:48.177
MR. ROSS, CAN YOU ADDRESS
THESE ALLEGATIONS?

30:58.107 --> 31:00.980
UH...NOT AT THIS TIME.

31:11.911 --> 31:14.163
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

31:14.163 --> 31:15.794
MARGAUX LEMARCHAL.

31:15.794 --> 31:18.377
MARGAUX, HI. LOUISE HERE.

31:18.377 --> 31:19.838
I JUST WANTED
TO CALL AND TELL YOU

31:19.838 --> 31:22.551
HOW GREAT
THE DAVID CLARKE PIECE WAS.

31:22.551 --> 31:24.633
I mean,
really riveting stuff.

31:24.633 --> 31:27.266
OH, THANK YOU.
VERY KIND OF YOU TO CALL.

31:27.266 --> 31:28.347
IT WAS --

31:28.347 --> 31:30.389
How did Victoria feel
about it?

31:30.389 --> 31:32.561
Victoria Grayson?

31:32.561 --> 31:34.773
I SUPPOSE SHE THOUGHT
IT WENT WELL.

31:34.773 --> 31:36.435
HMM.

31:36.435 --> 31:38.147
WELL, WE CAN TALK MORE
ABOUT IT TOMORROW.

31:38.147 --> 31:40.819
That is, if you're still up
for a rematch.

31:40.819 --> 31:41.981
YES.

31:41.981 --> 31:43.572
BY THE WAY,
HOW DID YOU KNOW

31:43.572 --> 31:46.195
I would be at the office
so late?

31:46.195 --> 31:47.987
OH,
I JUST TOOK A SHOT.

31:47.987 --> 31:51.120
You seem like one of those
workaholic types.

31:51.120 --> 31:52.831
Anyway, see you tomorrow.

31:52.831 --> 31:54.453
OKAY, BYE.

31:54.453 --> 31:56.415
[ RECEIVER CLICKS ]

31:59.168 --> 32:01.630
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

32:01.630 --> 32:04.803
YOUR MESSAGE SOUNDED
URGENT.

32:06.305 --> 32:08.007
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

32:08.007 --> 32:12.011
I JUST WANTED
TO SAY GOODBYE.

32:12.011 --> 32:13.182
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

32:13.182 --> 32:14.723
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

32:14.723 --> 32:16.395
I'M TAKING CONTROL
OF MY OWN LIFE.

32:16.395 --> 32:18.187
I'M CHECKING MYSELF
INTO REHAB.

32:18.187 --> 32:20.059
[ Chuckling ]
OH, CHARLOTTE!

32:20.059 --> 32:23.562
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
OH, THAT'S WONDERFUL!

32:23.562 --> 32:26.365
I KNOW SOME EXCELLENT
FACILITIES.

32:26.365 --> 32:29.068
WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'LL BE GOING? HMM?

32:29.068 --> 32:30.779
I'D RATHER NOT SAY,

32:30.779 --> 32:32.701
SINCE A LARGE PART
OF ME DOING THIS

32:32.701 --> 32:37.126
HAS TO DO WITH ME GETTING AWAY
FROM YOU AND YOUR LIES.

32:37.126 --> 32:41.080
DAVID DESERVES TO KNOW
THE TRUTH ABOUT EMILY.

32:41.080 --> 32:42.881
BUT DON'T WORRY.
I'M NOT GONNA SAY ANYTHING.

32:42.881 --> 32:44.083
IT'S YOUR LIE.

32:44.083 --> 32:46.925
I'M JUST NOT GONNA STICK AROUND
TO WATCH YOU TELL IT.

33:00.149 --> 33:03.102
I'M DOING WHAT'S BEST
FOR DAVID.

33:03.102 --> 33:05.104
WOULD YOU STOP?

33:05.104 --> 33:07.106
YOU'RE DOING THIS
TO HURT EMILY.

33:07.106 --> 33:08.197
CHARLOTTE, YOU KNOW ME.

33:08.197 --> 33:09.318
I THOUGHT I DID.

33:09.318 --> 33:12.111
AND THEN I FOUND OUT
YOU KILLED AIDEN.

33:12.111 --> 33:14.993
AND I KNOW WHY
YOU KILLED HIM --

33:14.993 --> 33:18.577
BECAUSE YOU BLAMED EMILY
FOR PASCAL'S DEATH.

33:18.577 --> 33:20.379
BUT HE DIED BECAUSE
SHE WAS SEEKING THE TRUTH

33:20.379 --> 33:22.291
ABOUT WHAT YOU DID
TO DAVID.

33:22.291 --> 33:24.213
I'M SICK OF BEING CAUGHT

33:24.213 --> 33:26.335
BETWEEN YOU AND EMILY
AND YOUR CYCLE OF HATE.

33:26.335 --> 33:28.547
I WANT OUT!

33:31.260 --> 33:35.684
WHAT I DID TO DAVID
ALL THOSE YEARS AGO...

33:35.684 --> 33:38.517
ALL THE THINGS
I HAVE DONE...

33:38.517 --> 33:39.848
I HAVE ACTED OUT OF LOVE,

33:39.848 --> 33:42.941
TO KEEP OUR FAMILY TOGETHER,
CHARLOTTE.

33:42.941 --> 33:44.063
FAMILY?

33:44.063 --> 33:45.854
LOOK AROUND YOU, MOTHER.

33:45.854 --> 33:48.487
THIS FAMILY YOU'VE BEEN WORKING
SO HARD TO KEEP TOGETHER --

33:48.487 --> 33:49.948
[ SNIFFLES ]

33:49.948 --> 33:51.240
YOU'VE DONE NOTHING
BUT TEAR US APART.

33:56.825 --> 33:59.208
[ Voice breaking ]
I LOVE YOU, BABY.

34:07.666 --> 34:09.717
David: SHE DIED NEVER KNOWING
THAT YOU'D BETRAYED HER,

34:09.717 --> 34:11.130
THAT YOU'D BETRAYED ME.

34:11.130 --> 34:14.092
FOR THAT,
I WILL NEVER FORGIVE YOU.

34:14.092 --> 34:16.975
Interviewer:
 MR. ROSS, CAN YOU ADDRESS
THESE ALLEGATIONS?

34:16.975 --> 34:18.726
[ SIGHS ]

34:18.726 --> 34:20.768
Nolan:
 NOT AT THIS TIME.

34:22.811 --> 34:24.773
[ SIGHS ]

34:26.565 --> 34:29.987
YEAH, YOU REALLY NEED
TO START CALLING FIRST.

34:29.987 --> 34:33.071
AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,
MY MONEY BOUGHT THIS HOUSE.

34:33.071 --> 34:35.324
YOU'RE JUST THE COWARD
WHO LIVES IN IT.

34:35.324 --> 34:38.496
HOW COULD YOU BELIEVE I WOULD DO
SOMETHING LIKE THAT...

34:38.496 --> 34:41.079
TO YOU, TO AMANDA?

34:41.079 --> 34:42.411
YOU KNOW ME, DAVID.

34:42.411 --> 34:43.962
I THOUGHT I DID.

34:43.962 --> 34:46.415
THE MAN I KNOW WOULDN'T HAVE
STOLEN MONEY FROM MY DAUGHTER.

34:46.415 --> 34:49.257
[ SIGHS ]
I DIDN'T KEEP THAT MONEY.

34:49.257 --> 34:51.880
OH, YEAH?
WHO'D YOU GIVE IT TO?

34:51.880 --> 34:54.513
I-I -- I G--
I GAVE IT TO AMANDA!

34:54.513 --> 34:56.135
BUT --
 BUT WHAT?

34:56.135 --> 34:57.716
OH, SHE BURNED THROUGH
$500 MILLION

34:57.716 --> 34:59.178
WITHOUT LEAVING A PAPER TRAIL?

34:59.178 --> 35:00.769
I WANT THE TRUTH, NOLAN.

35:00.769 --> 35:02.100
YEAH, SO DO I!

35:02.100 --> 35:05.184
YOU SAID THAT YOU WANTED ME
BY YOUR SIDE,

35:05.184 --> 35:07.146
THAT YOU BELIEVED IN ME!

35:07.146 --> 35:12.191
ALL AN ELABORATE TRAP
THAT YOU KNEW I WOULD FALL FOR

35:12.191 --> 35:13.902
BECAUSE I TRUST YOU
LIKE A FATHER.

35:13.902 --> 35:15.784
AAH!

35:15.784 --> 35:19.328
IF I WAS YOUR FATHER, I WOULD
HAVE DONE THAT A LONG TIME AGO.

35:19.328 --> 35:22.000
THEN YOU'RE MORE LIKE HIM
THAN I EVER REALIZED.

35:25.043 --> 35:26.205
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

35:35.384 --> 35:37.636
GOD.

35:37.636 --> 35:39.758
ARE YOU OKAY?
WHAT HAPPENED?

35:41.520 --> 35:43.312
[ SIGHS ]

35:43.312 --> 35:48.066
YOUR LIES...
FINALLY CAUGHT UP TO ME.

35:49.818 --> 35:51.770
[ SIGHS ]

36:14.002 --> 36:15.214
LOOKING FOR SOMETHING?

36:17.256 --> 36:18.347
YOU SCARED
THE HELL OUT OF ME.

36:18.347 --> 36:20.559
I THOUGHT YOU'D LEFT.

36:20.559 --> 36:22.140
AND I FIGURED YOU HADN'T.

36:22.140 --> 36:25.103
NOW YOU'RE BREAKING
INTO MOSTROWSKI'S GARAGE?

36:25.103 --> 36:27.226
JACK, LOOK,
IF YOU HAD ANY IDEA

36:27.226 --> 36:29.688
HOW MANY OF THESE THINGS
DIDN'T ADD UP HERE...

36:29.688 --> 36:32.901
YOU REALLY THINK THAT MOSTROWSKI
HAD SOMETHING TO DO WITH IT?

36:32.901 --> 36:34.733
I STUDIED THAT CASE FILE.

36:34.733 --> 36:35.984
WHEN MO WAS A SUSPECT,

36:35.984 --> 36:37.526
THEY PULLED HIS CREDIT CARD
AND HIS PHONE RECORDS.

36:37.526 --> 36:40.529
THE GUY HADN'T LEFT
A FIVE-MILE RADIUS IN TWO YEARS.

36:40.529 --> 36:43.201
HE NEVER TOLD PEOPLE
THAT HE WON IN ATLANTIC CITY

36:43.201 --> 36:44.413
BECAUSE HE DIDN'T WIN.

36:44.413 --> 36:46.285
THAT WAS JUST SOME STORY
HE TOLD TO HIS DAUGHTER

36:46.285 --> 36:48.497
TO EXPLAIN A SUDDEN WINDFALL
AND EARLY RETIREMENT.

36:48.497 --> 36:50.088
YEAH, MO WAS CLEARED
OF THE MURDER,

36:50.088 --> 36:51.960
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THAT HE DIDN'T PROVIDE

36:51.960 --> 36:53.592
AN ASSIST FOR SOMEONE
WHO PAID HIM OFF.

36:55.173 --> 36:56.885
SO WHAT ARE YOU DOING
OUT HERE?

36:56.885 --> 36:59.798
DENISE TOLD ME
HER DAD LIVED ALONE.

36:59.798 --> 37:01.890
BUT I SPOKE
WITH SOME OF THE NEIGHBORS,

37:01.890 --> 37:03.051
AND THEY TOLD ME
THAT THEY SAW SOMEONE

37:03.051 --> 37:04.683
COMING AND GOING
FROM THIS GARAGE

37:04.683 --> 37:07.185
OVER THE LAST
SEVERAL MONTHS.

37:07.185 --> 37:08.397
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

37:08.397 --> 37:11.059
SO I'M NOT LEAVING
UNTIL I SEARCH THIS PLACE.

37:22.781 --> 37:25.203
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

37:25.203 --> 37:28.206
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU MAKE A STRONG CASE.

37:28.206 --> 37:30.208
BUT LIKE I SAID,
WE'RE PARTNERS, SO...

37:30.208 --> 37:32.040
IF YOU'RE NOT
GONNA GIVE THIS UP,

37:32.040 --> 37:34.172
I GUESS I'M JUST GONNA
HAVE TO JOIN YOU.

37:37.045 --> 37:39.087
I'M REALLY PROUD OF YOU,
CHAR.

37:39.087 --> 37:42.050
WHAT FINALLY PUSHED YOU
TO MAKE A CHANGE?

37:42.050 --> 37:43.932
OUR MOTHER.

37:43.932 --> 37:45.934
OR, AT LEAST, THE THOUGHT
OF ME TURNING INTO OUR MOTHER.

37:45.934 --> 37:48.096
TRUST ME. I GET IT.

37:48.096 --> 37:49.808
EVERY TIME I LOOK
IN THE MIRROR,

37:49.808 --> 37:51.690
I'M TERRIFIED I'LL SEE DAD
STARING BACK.

37:51.690 --> 37:53.151
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:53.151 --> 37:55.153
BUT YOU'RE BETTER
THAN BOTH OF THEM.
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?

37:55.153 --> 37:58.196
YOU ARE, TOO.

37:58.196 --> 38:00.659
I DON'T KNOW WHERE
I'D BE WITHOUT YOU, DANIEL.

38:00.659 --> 38:03.031
PROBABLY STILL LISTENING
TO HILARY DUFF

38:03.031 --> 38:04.363
AND SURFING MYSPACE.

38:04.363 --> 38:05.364
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

38:05.364 --> 38:06.825
OUCH.
THE TRUTH HURTS.

38:06.825 --> 38:07.906
SERIOUSLY, THOUGH,

38:07.906 --> 38:10.208
THAT'S WHAT BIG BROTHERS
ARE FOR, RIGHT?

38:12.331 --> 38:16.835
HEY, YOU KNOW...

38:16.835 --> 38:20.088
YOU NEVER SHIED AWAY
FROM TELLING ME THE TRUTH,

38:20.088 --> 38:21.880
EVEN WHEN EVERYONE ELSE
WAS LYING TO ME.

38:23.382 --> 38:24.923
I LOVE YOU FOR THAT.

38:24.923 --> 38:27.846
THAT'S TRUE,

38:27.846 --> 38:30.018
AND I'D HATE TO LEAVE
ON A LIE.

38:31.350 --> 38:35.193
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE
I NEED TO TELL YOU.

38:35.193 --> 38:36.985
IT'S ABOUT EMILY.

38:38.817 --> 38:41.530
♪ OOH ♪

38:41.530 --> 38:44.943
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH ♪

38:44.943 --> 38:46.114
♪ AH, AH, AH ♪
 [ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

38:46.114 --> 38:48.827
♪ YOU COMPARE OUR LOVE
TO THE SUN ♪

38:48.827 --> 38:50.248
♪ WHAT HAVE YOU DONE? ♪
 [ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

38:50.248 --> 38:53.582
♪ THERE'S A LIMIT
TO THE PRIZES WE'VE WON ♪

38:53.582 --> 38:54.793
♪ ISN'T THE SAME ♪

38:54.793 --> 38:56.625
♪ DON'T GIVE IT A NAME ♪

38:56.625 --> 38:58.627
♪ LET ME REMAIN ♪

38:58.627 --> 39:02.010
♪ LET ME REMAIN ♪

39:02.010 --> 39:07.175
♪ I AM EVERYTHING
I HAVE EVER BEEN ♪

39:08.096 --> 39:10.018
♪ OOH, OOH-OOH, OOH ♪

39:10.018 --> 39:12.431
HI.

39:12.431 --> 39:14.683
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE SURE
THAT YOU WERE OKAY

39:14.683 --> 39:16.184
AFTER ALL
THAT TRANSPIRED.

39:16.184 --> 39:17.856
COME, SIT.

39:18.937 --> 39:21.029
I'M SORRY THAT I WAS DISTANT
THIS MORNING.

39:21.029 --> 39:23.532
IT WAS INTENTIONAL.

39:23.532 --> 39:25.944
I JUST COULDN'T RISK INVOLVING
YOU IN MY PLAN FOR NOLAN,

39:25.944 --> 39:29.908
SHOULD HE...
DECIDE TO RETALIATE.

39:29.908 --> 39:31.199
I SEE.

39:31.199 --> 39:35.794
WENT OVER TO SEE HIM
THIS EVENING.

39:35.794 --> 39:37.165
THINGS GOT OUT OF HAND.

39:37.165 --> 39:40.088
YOU WERE REACTING
ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD.

39:40.088 --> 39:42.711
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

39:42.711 --> 39:45.053
I KNOW THE FEELING WELL.

39:45.053 --> 39:48.637
NO.
IT'S MORE THAN THAT.

39:48.637 --> 39:50.138
AMANDA'S GONE.

39:52.060 --> 39:57.185
NOLAN WAS ONE OF THE FEW PEOPLE
FROM MY OLD LIFE...

39:57.185 --> 39:59.147
BEFORE IT GOT
RIPPED AWAY.

40:01.149 --> 40:05.113
NOW YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON LEFT
THAT CONNECTS ME TO MY PAST.

40:09.407 --> 40:13.291
I'LL ALWAYS BE HERE FOR YOU,
DAVID.

40:13.291 --> 40:14.453
ALWAYS.

40:17.245 --> 40:19.538
I HOPE YOU KNOW THAT.

40:30.348 --> 40:31.510
STAY WITH ME HERE TONIGHT.

40:34.222 --> 40:35.644
AND EVERY NIGHT.

40:39.558 --> 40:42.020
I WANT NOTHING MORE.

40:47.776 --> 40:50.448
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE DID THIS TO YOU.

40:50.448 --> 40:52.741
HE DIDN'T.

40:52.741 --> 40:56.204
YOU DID BECAUSE YOU'RE STILL
KEEPING HIM IN THE DARK.

40:56.204 --> 40:58.787
WAKE UP AND SMELL
THE SUBTEXT, EMILY.

40:58.787 --> 41:03.211
HE THINKS I STOLE MONEY
FROM AMANDA, ERGO YOU,

41:03.211 --> 41:05.884
BECAUSE HE'S STILL PROTECTING
THE MEMORY OF YOU

41:05.884 --> 41:08.006
BECAUSE HE LOVES YOU.

41:08.006 --> 41:10.048
IT'S TIME TO TELL HIM.

41:10.048 --> 41:11.049
I DON'T THINK WE CAN.

41:11.049 --> 41:12.090
WHY?

41:12.090 --> 41:14.182
NOT AFTER WHAT I DISCOVERED.

41:17.305 --> 41:20.649
THE GUY THAT CHARLOTTE KILLED
HAD THIS.

41:20.649 --> 41:23.231
I CONVINCED HER THAT HE WAS
JUST ANOTHER FLIGHT 197 FANATIC.

41:23.231 --> 41:24.442
YEAH,
BUT IF HE HAD BEEN,

41:24.442 --> 41:26.605
HE WOULD HAVE PUBLISHED
THIS PHOTO

41:26.605 --> 41:27.986
SO THE WORLD COULD SEE

41:27.986 --> 41:29.868
THAT KNOWN-TERRORIST
DAVID CLARKE WAS STILL ALIVE.

41:29.868 --> 41:31.449
WHO WAS THIS GUY?
 I DON'T KNOW.

41:31.449 --> 41:33.451
BUT HE WAS OBVIOUSLY FOLLOWING
HIM FOR QUITE SOME TIME.

41:33.451 --> 41:35.203
BUT WHY?
WHAT IS THE CONNECTION?

41:35.203 --> 41:37.325
YOUR FIELD TRIP DIDN'T PROVIDE
ANY ANSWERS?

41:37.325 --> 41:38.617
SURE DID.

41:38.617 --> 41:41.169
TURNS OUT, THE PLACE LEAKS
LIKE A SIEVE WHEN IT RAINS.

41:43.041 --> 41:46.424
SO, CONRAD'S SILO INSURANCE
DOESN'T COVER ROOF REPAIRS?

41:46.424 --> 41:48.386
THERE WAS RUST ON THE SINK,
ON THE WALLS,

41:48.386 --> 41:50.338
EVERYWHERE YOU WOULD IMAGINE
AFTER 10 YEARS,

41:50.338 --> 41:52.430
EXCEPT ON THE LEGS
OF HIS BED,

41:52.430 --> 41:56.635
EVEN THOUGH THEY WERE SITTING
IN A PUDDLE FROM THE RAIN.

41:56.635 --> 42:01.189
I THINK MY FATHER
WENT TO GREAT LENGTHS
TO STAGE THIS PLACE,

42:01.189 --> 42:03.061
BUT HE FAILED TO TAKE THE RAIN
INTO ACCOUNT.

42:03.061 --> 42:05.814
SO IF IT WAS STAGED --

42:05.814 --> 42:08.106
YOU THINK HE WAS NEVER THERE
AT ALL?

42:08.106 --> 42:10.358
IF HE'S LYING ABOUT THAT,

42:10.358 --> 42:13.411
THEN HE IS LYING
ABOUT EVERYTHING.
